Hi there,

Having an issue with the `UserInfoTokenServices`. I've got a Resource Server configured using `@EnableOAuth2Resource` and I've setup the `spring.oauth2.resource.userInfoUri` property to point to the '/me' endpoint on my separate Auth Server. From the logs, I see that the request, the `OAuth2AuthenticationProcessingFilter` processes, successfully authenticates but with the 'Granted Authorities: USER_ROLE' even though my user doesn't have that role. 

In my `HttpSecurity` on the `ResourceServerConfigurerAdapter` class, I restrict access to my API based on `ROLE_ADMIN` and as such I always get an 'Access Denied' response.

Had a look at the `UserInfoTokenServices` and when the `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken` is created in the `extractAuthenticaton()` method, the `Collection<GrantedAuthority>` is always set to: `AuthorityUtils.commaSeparatedStringToAuthorityList("ROLE_USER"))`.

I had a go at implementing a method to extract the authorities from the `userInfoEndpointUrl` response map:

``` java
    private String[] getAuthorities(Map<String, Object> map) {
        @SuppressWarnings("unchecked")
        List<Map<String, String>> authorityList = (List<Map<String, String>>) map.get("authorities");

        List<String> authorities = new ArrayList<>();
        for (Map<String, String> authority : authorityList) {
            authorities.add(authority.get("authority"));
        }
        return authorities.toArray(new String[] {});
    } 
```

This seems to work when I feed that into the `UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken`:

```
UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken user = new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken(getPrincipal(map), "N/A", AuthorityUtils.createAuthorityList(getAuthorities(map)));
```

Is this an issue with the `UserInfoTokenServices`? Or am I just missing something in the configuration?

Cheers,
Nuno

